title: CBS Sports 128: Clemson overtakes Ohio State at No. 1; Memphis, USC soar
text:
CBS Sports 128 Rank Team 1. Clemson 2. Ohio State 3. Baylor 4. LSU 5. Alabama 6. Michigan State 7. Stanford 8. Iowa 9. Notre Dame 10. TCU 11. Oklahoma State 12. Florida 13. Oklahoma 14. Utah 15. Memphis 16. Houston 17. Florida State 18. Michigan 19. Toledo 20. Ole Miss 21. Temple 22. Duke 23. UCLA 24. USC 25. North Carolina Check out the teams ranked 26-128 . CBS Sports 128: 1-25 | 26-128 
With four touchdowns on its first four possessions, Clemson blew the doors off Sun Life Stadium and cruised to a 58-0 win against Miami that resulted in Al Golden's dismissal and the Tigers' rise to No. 1 in the new CBS Sports 128 rankings. 
Clemson jumps four spots from No. 5, leaping Ohio State, Baylor and LSU, which round out the top four following victories of their own in Week 8. Utah, previously at No. 4, falls to No. 14 after losing to USC; Florida State also tumbles from No. 8 to No. 17 after Georgia Tech's incredible blocked field goal return touchdown . 
Michigan State moves up four spots to No. 6 by pulling away late from Indiana, and it seems like our voters are starting to trust undefeated Oklahoma State, as the Cowboys soar up seven spots to No. 11 after trouncing Kansas. 
Other than a few minor adjustments and a new No. 1, Week 8 gave us some highlights and news but no major shakeups in the top 25 of the CBS Sports 128.
Texas A&M and Cal drop out of the top 25 after losses to No. 5 Alabama and No. 23 UCLA, respectively. USC, at 4-3, sneaks in at No. 24 due to its dominant victory over Utah, and North Carolina makes its debut at No. 25 after beating Virginia to improve to 6-1. 
Here's a breakdown how each conference fares in the top 25 of the CBS Sports 128 (highest-ranked team in parenthesis):
ACC: 4 (No. 1 -- Clemson)
Big Ten: 4 (No. 2 -- Ohio State)
Big 12: 4 (No. 3 -- Baylor)
SEC: 4 (No. 4 -- LSU)
Pac-12: 4 (No. 7 -- Stanford)
American: 3 (No. 15 -- Memphis)
Independent: 1 (No. 9 -- Notre Dame)
MAC: 1 (No. 19 -- Toledo)
Clemson took over the top spot in the CBS Sports 128 after routing Miami 58-0.
